Spain remains Britons ' favourite destination to fly to , as it has been for more than 25 years .
New figures from the UK Civil Aviation Authority shows 238m passengers passed through British airports in 2014 , just three million less than the pre-recession boom peak of 241m in 2007 .
Germany proved a more visited destination than France and the US ahead of Spain and the Netherlands .
There has been a rise of 2.3 per cent in passengers flying to and from North America .